article.description: Adam Flagler scored 16 points, Francois Lewis added 15 and Presbyterian beat North Carolina A&T 75-70 on Saturday.
article.headline: Presbyterian beats North Carolina A&T 75-70
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Adam Flagler scored 16 points, Francois Lewis added 15 and Presbyterian beat North Carolina A&T 75-70 on Saturday. Chris Martin made a pair of free throws with 22 seconds left to give the Blue Hose (4-4) a 73-70 lead. The Aggies' Terry Harris missed a 3-point attempt with nine seconds left and JC Younger made two more free throws to ice it for Presbyterian. The Blue Hose trailed 39-36 at the half and traded the lead with North Carolina A&T until going on an 8-0 run to lead 66-59 on Flagler's jumper with 4:09 left. The Blue Hose never trailed again, but the Aggies (2-6) closed the deficit to 71-70 on Amari Hamilton's 3-pointer with 32 seconds left. Younger added 11 points for the Blue Hose. Harris made 8 of 11 from 3-point range and scored 27 for the Aggies. Kameron Langley added 10 points.
